  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>SPACElogic Pte Ltd is a young & dynamic organisation that specialises in interior design & fit-out, permanent exhibits & display, signage & environmental graphics and event & exhibition projects.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Lead the management and execution of tender and contract processes within the interior design and fit-out sector, ensuring compliance, effective contractor evaluation, and timely certification of progress claims to drive project success.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Analyze and interpret tender contract requirements to ensure alignment with project objectives and compliance standards</li><li>Review tender scope of works and bills of quantity to validate accuracy and completeness for submission</li><li>Prepare and submit comprehensive tender documentation to meet client and regulatory expectations</li><li>Manage contract documentation and related administrative matters to maintain project integrity and legal compliance</li><li>Evaluate and negotiate with contractors to secure optimal terms and performance outcomes</li><li>Certify contractors’ progress claims by assessing work completion and verifying compliance with contract terms</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Quantity Surveying, Building, or Civil Engineering</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications to produce accurate reports and documentation</li><li>Skilled in PlanSwift and Adobe Acrobat for precise measurement and document management</li><li>Proficiency in BIM software (Bonus) to support digital project coordination</li><li>Demonstrated strong interpersonal, communication, and copywriting skills to facilitate clear stakeholder engagement</li><li>Capable of conflict management and problem-solving to resolve project challenges effectively</li><li>Interest in the interior and exhibition industry (Bonus) to align with company focus and culture</li><li>At least 2-4 years’ relevant experience in the interior industry in Singapore demonstrating practical knowledge and application</li><li>Independent work ethic with a positive attitude and strong sense of responsibility</li></ul>",
